title: For Sale/Trade:  Excellent (LNIB?) FNH FNS 9 w/ night sights, 2 holsters
postcontent:
For sale or trade, one nearly-new FNH FNS 9mm with all factory accessories - case, backstraps, 3 mags, etc. - and two holsters (Desantis OWB leather, Zero Concealment Systems kydex OWB, both RH). I bought this new a few months ago back in November. Test fire date April of 2013. Approx 300 rounds downrange, all flawless. 

Factory night sights (really nice, defined sight picture!), fully ambidextrous controls, great texture on the grip, flat and curved backstraps (natural pointer for me with the flat, like a 1911 with flat mainspring housing or 3rd gen Smith, love that!)... I can't really say enough good things about this gun. 

I actually feel that this is put together more robustly than a Glock (gasp!), kinda over-built (guess that's what you get from a military arms manufacturer!). 

But I have (finally?) realized that I just prefer compacts and sub-compacts for my guns, and that's that. This FNS grip actually fits my hands better and feels better than any other full-size gun has - but I just want something smaller. For someone bigger than me, or for range or dedicated HD use (or you OC guys and gals!), with its 17+1 capacity, it's great!

Here's a couple of videos that do a great job showing off the FNS (although both of them are manual safety models, mine's without):

http://youtu.be/WEbWnuKixTk

http://youtu.be/dNd7er5BM04

Cash price for the whole package $450, or trade for LNIB Glock 26 Gen 4 with all factory stuff like included here. Like condition Smith J-frame (no lock) 38/357 or Ruger LCR 38/357 considered as well.

FTF only within 40 miles of Marshall Co. Show IN DL and LTCH, nothing recorded. 

Pics taken from my iPhone with not-so-great lighting, but you get the idea. If you need better resolution or detail about something, let me know.

title: For Sale:  Spyderco Military CRUWEAR Sprint Run
postcontent:
BRAND NEW IN BOX. UNUSED.

This Military Model Sprint features a conventional Military Model PlainEdge blade-profile with a flat-grind and oversized blade hole. Machined onto the blade’s spine and choil are sections of jimping that inhibit the knife from slipping forward or backward when forcefully cutting or sawing.

The blade is matched with peel ply grey G-10 handle and a Michael Walker LinerLock®. The lock's liner is nested into the scale which augments lock strength without having to rely on bulkier full-length internal liners.

Crucible Steel Company produces performance automotive, aerospace, defense, and consumer-products steels. They also manufacture high-performance steels for the knife industry. Recently they presented Spyderco the opportunity to be the first production knife company to offer CPM® CRU-WEAR® to the public. A CPM® CRU-WEAR® Military Model Sprint Run became a reality. 

CPM® CRU-WEAR® steel is an air-hardened powdered metallurgy tool steel. Crucible’s original smelted-produced CRU-WEAR® was created as an upgrade to A2 and D2 tool steels, both have earned longevity and respect in the cutlery business for their wear resistance and tough cutting performance. 

Powder produced CPM® CRU-WEAR® ups the ante. Through powdered steel technology, the steel is made easier to machine with improved resistance to chipping over the original smelted CRU-WEAR®. The powdered variety also attains a higher hardness factor through greater percentages of tungsten and molybdenum that result in a secondary hardening response.

title: For Sale:  WINCHESTER MODEL 1895 DELUXE NEARLY NEW ORIGINAL CONDITION!!
location: North Carolina, North Carolina, United States
postcontent: This Winchester is one of the finest original Model 1895 Deluxe rifles is existance! This is the Winchester model that Theodore Roosevelt made famous in his around the world hunting exploits. Made & shipped in 1902 it is truly a special order rifle which has remained in near new ORIGINAL condition for over 100 years. Copy of Winchester Cody Firearms Museum record pictured for this gun....it letters right down to the special order sights! This gun was ordered in the powerful .35 Winchester caliber. The grain and figure in the fancy checkered buttstock and forend is fantastic..plimented by the original OIL FINISH. Hard rubber shotgun buttplate. Minor handling marks are present in the wood commensurate with 100 years of gentle handling. No cracks or chips or extra holes. The original blue on this gun is nearly all there with a slightest amount of wear on the right side of box magazine where the lever mechanism has travelled a few times. The receiver of this gun has the deepest rich blue that I have ever seen on a Winchester. The Winchester factory craftsmen who worked on this special order rifle obviously spent extra time with it's polish. All edges & corners are razor sharp & crisp! Screws are untouched. This gun still retains the case color on the hammer and brilliant case color on the trigger block mechanism which I have never seen remaining on a Model 1895. The special order Lyman sights add to the charm of this near new Deluxe. At some point long ago the sight filler blank on the barrel was upgraded to a proper Winchester rear sight. This is a wonderful opportunity to acquire a nearly new Deluxe rifle. It is a "blue-chip" investment grade Winchester for the advanced collector. A special order gun in this condition will continue to appreciate for a collector OR savy investor.

A beautifull rifle reflecting a unique period in Australian shooting history, where many excess 303's were "sporterized" for Kangaroo and varmit shooting etc. The yanks may call it a Wildcat......you definitey won't find another like it.

Specifically designed and customized for Kangaroo shooting in Australia....commonly known as the 303/25. (British 303 with 0.25"bullet) Shoots flat up to 400yds via 87grain bullet. Lower grain by design to minimize pelt damage as roo skins fetched good money back in those days.

Based on the 1904 Lee Enfield Mk1 ShtlLE with Markings reflecting the reign of King Edward. Customized Desert Oak Stock and Forestock with rare cheek saddle carved in the Stock.
Nikko Scope
5 Shot magazine
Some original 87grain ammo from Australia in original box, and some customized higher grain 303/25 Ammo.
Die for necking the 303 shells down to 0.25.

Contact Jeff at REDACTED Calls Only....DO NOT EMAIL...Cash Only

Call me if you want more pics and I can email to you.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Turk and Brazilian Mauser, and Norinco SKS
postcontent:
Greetings folks. I am having to clear some space in the cabinet and have 3 pieces of the collection up for sale/trade. I am looking for either cash, Mosin Nagants, or German Mausers.

1) 1944 Turkish K. Khale 8mm Mauser. Typical Turk mis-match. One of the smoothest actions that I've ever had. It passes the bullet test with plenty of room to spare. Strong lands with shine, and darker grooves with very light frost in places (unfortunately standard for many Turks). It does have a cleaning rod, though no bayonet or sling. Stock has only a few minor marks on it, and shows darker in spots from honest handling. Bluing is ~90-95% **has excellent head spacing** Asking $300

2) Early 1980s pre-ban Norinco import SKS with spike bayonet. All matching. Only ~400 rounds through it. Still has cleaning kit in stock, but missing cleaning rod. Asking $400

3) Mauser 1908 Brazilian long rifle, mfg - Deutsche Waffen UND, Munitionsfabriken Oberndorf aN, in 7mm Mauser, original matching numbers on barrel and bolt. Still retains capture screws. 80% overall blue, very light beginnings of patina developing on floor plate, trigger guard, and receiver/bolt. Otherwise, receiver is still in the white. It has a strong Brazilian Star crest, very good ++ bore-bright & shiny-strong lands and grooves. No import mark but no cleaning rod. Very good walnut stock with a German-style ring for bolt dis-assembly rather than the standard disk, has the usual dings and dents but still solid. Slight damage, likely from moisture, at the top of the butt plate. **good head space and no import mark**Asking $400
